                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.34112A/9–2244: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-22T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 22, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 23—12:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>537. The Minister for Foreign Affairs informed me this morning Paraguayan
                    Government is desirous of cooperating in sense of Department’s circular telegram
                    September 20, 5 p.m.<note n="80" xml:id="d1410fn80">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_530">p. 530</ref>.</note> I
                    discussed with him in principle possible absorption by Bank of Paraguay of Banco
                    Germánico and forced sale of spearhead Axis firms and he expressed a desire to
                    discuss matters in detail. I said if temporary financing were needed to carry
                    out some of these operations I should be glad to explore possibility of such
                    financing by an agency of our Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
